solutions.content:
If we linearly arrange all the elements of each row of a matrix , we will have an array. 
Add k to the current index of the array and convert that index to represent grid indices.

A m*n matrix can be converted into an array or matrix can be represented in the form of a long array
			matrix[ i ][ j ] = arr[ i*n + j ]
An element in the long array of size m*n , can be taken into the form of matrix or into matrices indices using
			arr[ i ] = matrix[ i / n ][ i % n ];
Time Complexity of below code: O( m * n )
Space Complexity of below code : O( m * n )
```
    vector<vector<int>> shiftGrid(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int k) {
        int m = grid.size();
        int n = grid[0].size();
        vector<vector<int>> res(m, vector<int>(n, -1));

        int low = 0, high = m*n;
        for(int i = 0; i < high; i++){
            int ni = ( (i+k)%high ) / n;
            int nj = ( (i+k)%high ) % n;

            res[ni][nj] = grid[i/n][i%n];
        }
        return res;
    }
```
