If the tree is not too sparse, using a bitset uses less memory than an unordered_set. I think it amounts to only 8KiB, given the problem's upper node limit, enough to fit entirely in the CPU's cache. I also expect element access to compare favorably with an unordered_set's.
If lots of small trees are to be expected, preallocating a full-size bitset may be a pessimization, but replacing it with a (dynamic-sized) vector is fairly straightforward.

