**Non DP**
Calculate the sum of all numbers. During that iterate, find:
- smallest number that % 3 == 1
- second smallest number that % 3 == 1
- smallest number that % 3 == 2
- second smallest number that % 3 == 2

if `sum % 3 == 0`, return it.

if `sum % 3 == 1`, either subtract it by `smallest1` or `smallest2 + second_smallest2`, to get a number that % 3 == 0. Return number after subtraction.

if `sum % 3 == 2`, either subtract it by `smallest2` or `smallest1 + second_smallest1`, to get a number that % 3 == 0. Return number after subtraction.


```
class Solution {
    public int maxSumDivThree(int[] nums) {
        int sum = 0;
        int f1 = 1_000_0000, s1 = 1_000_0000, f2 = 1_000_0000, s2 = 1_000_0000;
        for (int num : nums) {
            sum += num;
            if (num % 3 == 1) {
                if (num < f1) {
                    s1 = f1;
                    f1 = num;
                } else if (num < s1) {
                    s1 = num;
                }
            } else if (num % 3 == 2) {
                if (num < f2) {
                    s2 = f2;
                    f2 = num;
                } else if (num < s2) {
                    s2 = num;
                }
            }
        }

        if (sum % 3 == 0) return sum;

        if (sum % 3 == 1) {
            return sum - Math.min(f1, f2+s2);
        } else {
            return sum - Math.min(f2, f1+s1);
        }
    }
}
