solutions.content:
# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Find the total sum of the array. 

### If sum % 3 == 0: 
return the sum

### If sum % 3 == 1:
The answer will be
* (sum - smallest number whose remainder is 1 when divided by 3)

* (sum - first smallest number whose remainder is 2 - second smallest number whose remainder is 2)

* Return the maximum of these two

### If sum % 3 == 2:
The answer will be

* (sum - smallest number whose remainder is 2 when divided by 3)

* (sum - first smallest number whose remainder is 1 - second smallest number whose remainder is 1)

* Return the maximum of these two








# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Iterate through the array to find the total sum. When iterating through the array also find the first and second smallest numbers whose remainder is 1 and 2.

For sum % 3 == 1 and sum % 3 == 2 before returning check if the necessary first and second min are set


