/*
Here I have used a simple concepts of division, if remainder is subtracted from the dividend the divisor will completely divide the dividend.
eg:
4%3=1
4-1=3
3%3=0
likewise,
5%3=2
5-2=3
3%3=0

According to the above mentioned approach, we traverse the array and find the sum of all the elements of the array, along with keeping the track of, minimum element that gives 1 and minimum number that gives 2 as remainder.

At the end, if;

sum%3=0;  return sum
sum%3=1; return (sum-minimum element minimum element that gives 1 as remainder).
sum%3=2; return (sum-minimum element minimum element that gives 1 as remainder).

Thus maximum sum divisible by 3 is returned.

*/


```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxSumDivThree(vector<int>& nums) {
        int sum=0,sum1=20000,sum2=20000;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            sum+=nums[i];
            if(nums[i]%3==1){
                sum2=min(sum2,nums[i]+sum1);
                sum1=min(sum1,nums[i]);

            }
            else if(nums[i]%3==2){
                sum1=min(sum1,sum2+nums[i]);
                sum2=min(sum2,nums[i]);
            }
        }

        switch(sum%3){
            case 0:{
                break;
            }
            case 1:{
                return (sum-sum1);
                //break;
                }
            case 2:{
                return (sum-sum2);
                //break;
            }
        }
        return sum;

    }
};
```

