1. Take the sum of complete array and see by how much does it exceed from the nearest multiple of  3 (take mod of this sum with 3 and see what is the remainder)
2. Select a set of numbers which can offset this value and bring sum to a multiple of 3 by ejecting these numbers. In other words find shortest set of values whose sum gives same remainder as the total sum on taking mod with 3. To find these shortest values we need to sort the array,
3. If sum%3==0 just return this sum.
4. If sum%3==1:  Either eject the smallest number with num%3==1 or two numbers with num%3==2 (since (2+2)%3 is also 1) so that we lose this extra 1 as remainder from total sum. We need to consider both of these possibilities as there might be two very small numbers with mod 2 in the array and the first number with mod 1 might be bigger than combined sum of such small numbers.
5. Similarly if sum%3==2 either remove smallest number with num%3==2 or two numbers with num%3==1 whichever does less damage to out sum. Below is my code:

		class Solution {
			public int maxSumDivThree(int[] nums) {
			Arrays.sort(nums);
			int sum=0;
			for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
				sum+=nums[i];
			}
			int rem= sum%3;

			//if sum is already divisible by 3 return this sum
			if(rem==0)
				return sum;

			//sum of numbers we want to throw out so total sum becomes a multiple of 3. 
			//This should be as low as possible
			int eject=0;

			//if remainder exceeds by 1 either eject one number with mod=1 or two numbers with mod=2 so that (2+2)%3=1 
			if(rem==1) eject=Math.min(one1(nums),two2(nums));

			//same logic as above but we either need to throw 2 numbers with mod 1 each or one number with mod 2
			else       eject=Math.min(one2(nums),two1(nums));

			return sum-eject;
			}

			private int one1(int[] nums){
				for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++)
					if(nums[i]%3==1)
						return nums[i];
			return Integer.MAX_VALUE;
			}

			private int two2(int[] nums){
			int first=0,second=0;

			for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
				if(nums[i]%3==2 && first==0)
					first=nums[i];
				else if(nums[i]%3==2){
					second=nums[i]; break;
				}
			}
			if(first==0 || second==0)
				return Integer.MAX_VALUE;
			return first+second;
