Any number will be a sum of 3 if (sum%3 == 0)

Let's say x = (sum % 3) and x != 0.
then to make the sum divisble by 3, we have to subtract x from sum (i.e. alpha = sum-x) and hence alpha will be divisble by 3.

Thus our task is to find greatest value of alpha, which in  turn implies we have to find smallest value of x.

-> x can have two values either 1 or 2. (sum%3)/
Thus our task is to find smalles number in the whole array having remainder as 1 or 2. And subtract that number from the total sum of the array.

```
class Solution {
    public int maxSumDivThree(int[] nums) {
        int rem1=10001;
        int rem2=10001;
        int n = nums.length;
        int sum=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            sum+=nums[i];
            if(nums[i]%3==1) {
                rem2 = Math.min(rem1+nums[i], rem2);
                rem1 = Math.min(rem1, nums[i]);
            }
            if(nums[i]%3==2) {
                rem1 = Math.min(rem2+nums[i], rem1);
                rem2 = Math.min(rem2, nums[i]);
            }

        }
        if (sum % 3 == 0) {
            return sum;
        }
        return sum%3==1 ? (sum-rem1) : (sum-rem2);
    }
}
