solutions.content:
Get the sum of all numbers in the array first. Then we have 3 cases:
1. If sum % 3 == 0
    return sum directly.
2. If sum % 3 == 1
    What we want to do is to find out the smallest sub array in the origin array whose sum mod 3 is also 1.
	So that we can get the final answer: sum - sub_sum.
	The only 2 cases for the sub_sum which mod 3 is 1:
    * 	The smallest number which mod 3 is 1.
    * 	The smallest 2 numbers which mod 3 is 2. (if a % 3 == 2 and b % 3 == 2, (a + b) % 3 will be 1)

	Once we get above 2 sub sums, just need to compare which one is smaller and minus this sub sum.
3. If sum % 3 == 2
    The same idea as #2.


Add an example here.

If we have an array like: 7, 5, 4, 2, 9, 10, 6, 3, 1.
The solution here is to sum up all the numbers together, which is 47.
And also get the smallest 2 numbers who mod 3 is 1 and 2, which are `min_remain_one`= 1, `min_remain_one_2`= 4 and `min_remain_two`= 2, `min_remain_two_2`= 5.
As 47 mod 3 is 2, then we compare `min_remain_two`= 2 with `min_remain_one` + `min_remain_one_2` = 5, get `min_remain_two` is smaller. So that the final result is 47 - 2 = 45.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxSumDivThree(vector<int>& nums) {
        int min_remain_one = INT_MAX;
        int min_remain_two = INT_MAX;
        int min_remain_one_2 = INT_MAX;
        int min_remain_two_2 = INT_MAX;
        int sum = 0;

        for (int num : nums) {
            int remain = num % 3;

            switch (remain) {
                case 1:
                    if (num <= min_remain_one) {
                        min_remain_one_2 = min_remain_one;
                        min_remain_one = num;
                    } else if (num <= min_remain_one_2) {
                        min_remain_one_2 = num;
                    }
                    break;
                case 2:
                    if (num <= min_remain_two) {
                        min_remain_two_2 = min_remain_two;
                        min_remain_two = num;
                    } else if (num <= min_remain_two_2) {
                        min_remain_two_2 = num;
                    }
                    break;
            }

            sum += num;
        }

        if (sum % 3 == 1) {
            if (min_remain_two == INT_MAX || min_remain_two_2 == INT_MAX)
                sum -= min_remain_one;
            else
                sum -= min(min_remain_one, min_remain_two + min_remain_two_2);
        } else if (sum % 3 == 2) {
            if (min_remain_one == INT_MAX || min_remain_one_2 == INT_MAX)
                sum -= min_remain_two;
            else
                sum -= min(min_remain_two, min_remain_one + min_remain_one_2);
        }

        return sum;
    }
};
